body.content:
The amendment introduced the following three options of punishment for drug possession: 

                  1. Incarceration for up to three years; 

                  2. Incarceration for six months to five years  for considerable quantities of drugs; 

                  3. Fine or incarceration for up to one year in cases of lesser gravity (Stasiowski 2009). 

                  The 2000 law hampered needle and syringe programs by undermining their legality. According to some researchers (e.g. Malinowska-Sempruch 2013) the law constructed a new type of a criminal - a drug user.
